; Resolve all packages through the Microsoft package-feed proxy instead of the
; public npm registry. It screens for supply-chain / 0-day-vulnerable packages
; before they enter the build. Mirror this in the global npm/pnpm registry on
; each machine (see the README "Development" section).
;
; NB: the repo intentionally has NO `packageManager` field in package.json — with
; the proxy, pnpm/Corepack cannot self-provision a pinned pnpm version (the proxy
; doesn't serve pnpm's self-resolution in the required integrity-only form), so we
; use whatever pnpm is installed. Provision pnpm via your base image / global install.
registry=https://packagefeedproxy.microsoft.io/npm/
